== Description == <!--T:3-->

The [[Image:BIM_Shape2DView.svg|24px]] [[BIM_Shape2DView|BIM Shape2DView]] tool creates a 2D projection of the selected objects on the XY-plane.

It is a specialized wrapper around the [[Draft_Shape2DView|Draft Shape2DView]] tool, tailored for architectural workflows. While the Draft tool keeps the 2D projection in its original 3D position by default, the BIM tool explicitly forces the {{PropertyData|InPlace}} property to {{FALSE}}. This strips the projection of its 3D spatial context, flattening it onto the global XY plane (at Z=0).

This behavior is specifically designed to work with an [[Arch_SectionPlane|Arch SectionPlane]] to generate  2D architectural drawings (such as floor plans and elevations) that can be easily grouped in a [[BIM_DrawingView|BIM DrawingView]], exported to DXF/SVG, or inserted into a [[TechDraw_Workbench|TechDraw]] page. To generate the solid fills for intersected walls, use the companion [[BIM_Shape2DCut|BIM Shape2DCut]] tool.

For more info, see the [[Arch_SectionPlane#Typical_drawing_workflow|typical BIM drawing workflow]].

